Set your Pricing Framework



1. Costs shouldn't be a factor in deciding the Price

2. Use the DMU and the Process to Acquire a paying sutomer to idnetify key price points

3. Understand the Prices of the Customer's Alternatives

4. Different TYpes of customers will pay different Prices

5. Be flexible with Pricing for Early Testers / Lighthouse customers

6. It is always easier to DROP the price than RAISE the price